data.text:
Other Related Indexes

To view the FIRST index (only) of Emigrants to NSW from the period 1828 - 1855 , click on : TIPPERARY EMIGRANT DATABASE 1828 - 1855 To view the SECOND index (only) of Emigrants to NSW from the period 1856 - 1866 , click on : TIPPERARY EMIGRANT DATABASE 1856 - 1866 To view the combined index of Emigrants to NSW from 1828 - 1865,click on : TIPPERARY EMIGRANT DATABASE 1828 - 1866 To view the list of nearly 300 people who were ALMOST Emigrants , but never actually came ,click on: ALMOST EMIGRANT DATABASE A little research on convicts from Tipperary has been lent to me , and you can view it on : Convict research The "Family Links" page can be found at : Tipperary Family Links The Tipperary Emigrants Death Page can be found at : Deaths of Tipperary Emigrants You are very welcome to make contributions to these pages, as the data will need to come from those who HAVE it. Send any details that you'd like to share to Peter at : [email protected] Got any questions about this database ? Check out the "Frequently Asked Questions" Page at FAQ

What's next ??

Whenever useful info comes my way , I'll try to form it into a page that complements this one.

Marriages of Tipperary People in Victoria:

The information in the first 4 columns comes from Victorian BDM discs and microfiche of shipping arrivals (assisted). The first person mentioned is definitely an immigrant from Tipperary. If the same marriage is listed in reverse order, then BOTH people came from Tipperary.
